The paper discusses the use of empowerment in reinforcement learning, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments are conducted in robotics domains, which falls under the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the convergence of the empowered values, which is related to control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a unified Bellman optimality principle, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
